<%- include('partials/header') %>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/phantom-twin.css">
<nav class="navbar">
        <div class="nav-container">
            <a href="#" class="nav-brand">THE PHANTOM <span>TWIN</span></a>
            <button class="nav-toggle" id="navToggle" aria-label="Toggle navigation">≡</button>
            <ul class="nav-links" id="navLinks">
                <li><a href="#story">Story</a></li>
                <li><a href="#characters">Characters</a></li>
                <li><a href="#chapters">Chapters</a></li>
                <li><a href="#quotes">Quotes</a></li>
                <li><a href="#journey">Journey</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <header class="hero">
        <div class="hero-container">
            <div class="hero-content">
                <p class="hero-author">A Novel Experience</p>
                <h1 class="hero-title">The Phantom Twin</h1>
                <p class="hero-tagline">"Consistency is god. I am its priest."</p>
                <p class="hero-hook">
                    In the rain-glazed, glass city of Valora, brilliant data analyst Aarav Deshmukh plays a divine game of psychological mastery. To prove that reality is merely a consensus shaped by repetition and cognitive bias, he engineers the ultimate algorithm: a phantom twin brother who takes the blame for a dark, calculated correction.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="hero-cover-wrapper">
                <div class="book-cover-shadow"></div>
                <img class="book-poster" src="https://cdn-gcs.inkitt.com/vertical_storycovers/9601465eab806ae27d95c1b28211eb49.jpg" alt="The Phantom Twin Book Poster">
            </div>
        </div>
        <a href="#story" class="scroll-indicator" aria-label="Scroll to story details">
            <div class="mouse"><div class="wheel"></div></div>
            <span>Enter the Illusion</span>
        </a>
    </header>

    <main>
        <section id="story" class="section-padding">
            <div class="story-layout">
                <div class="synopsis-block">
                    <span class="section-label">The Concept</span>
                    <h2 class="section-heading">The Anatomy of Perceptual Dominance</h2>
                    <div class="highlighted-quote">
                        "If reality is consensus, then deception is merely advanced persuasion."
                    </div>
                    <div class="synopsis-text">
                        <p>
                            Aarav Deshmukh is a twenty-four-year-old architectural prodigy of the mind. Operating with cold, clinical certainty, he views humanity as predictable systems driven by base biological scripts. To him, thought is a sport, prediction an art, and societal consensus a malleable entity waiting to be rewritten by supreme intellect.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            What begins as a subtle social experiment—casually planting whispers of an unstable, impulsive twin brother named Arjun to neighbors, coworkers, and friends—evolves into an intricate, tactile algorithm of deception. Through pre-recorded calls, dual digital footprints, meticulously forged synthetic fingerprints, and calculated public alterations, the ghost takes form. The world does not crave truth; it craves a story, and Aarav builds an unbreakable one.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            But the illusion harbors a darker purpose. It is a calculated rehearsal for absolute equilibrium. Guided by a tragic past and an unyielding thirst for systemic correction, Aarav positions his phantom shadow to shoulder the weight of an unpardonable crime—the clinical elimination of Raghav Malhotra, the corrupt tycoon who destroyed his father's life.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="themes-container">
                        <h4 class="serif-font" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--accent-gold);">Core Elements Explored</h4>
                        <ul class="theme-list">
                            <li class="theme-tag">Psychological Manipulation</li>
                            <li class="theme-tag">Confirmation Bias</li>
                            <li class="theme-tag">Duality of Identity</li>
                            <li class="theme-tag">Mathematical Retribution</li>
                            <li class="theme-tag">The Fragility of Consensus</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="stats-grid">
                    <div class="stat-card">
                        <span class="stat-value">6+</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">Chapters Compiled</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card">
                        <span class="stat-value">1</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">Mastermind Narrator</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card">
                        <span class="stat-value">Months</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">Temporal Span</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card">
                        <span class="stat-value">Thriller</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">Literary Genre</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="characters" class="characters-bg">
            <div class="section-padding">
                <span class="section-label">The Players</span>
                <h2 class="section-heading">Architects & Observers</h2>
                <div class="characters-grid">
                    <div class="character-card">
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="character-name">Aarav Deshmukh / Suryan</h3>
                            <div class="character-role">The Conductor</div>
                            <p class="character-desc">
                                A hyper-brilliant, twenty-four-year-old data analyst who possesses a rare, clinical ability to identify patterns, probabilities, and human vulnerabilities. Behind his polite, calculated exterior lies a profound, detached certainty that he is an elite architect meant to rise above the chaotic masses.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="traits-wrapper">
                            <span class="trait-tag">Methodical</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Hyper-Rational</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Detached</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Surgical</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="character-card">
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="character-name">Arjun / "The Twin"</h3>
                            <div class="character-role">The Fabricated Shadow</div>
                            <p class="character-desc">
                                The impulsive, reckless, and dangerous alter-ego manufactured entirely by Aarav. Designed as the perfect structural contrast to Aarav's disciplined persona, he exists purely within the minds, expectations, and confirmation biases of the public, serving as the ultimate scapegoat.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="traits-wrapper">
                            <span class="trait-tag">Volatile</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Reckless</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Chaotic</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Phantom Entity</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="character-card">
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="character-name">Inspector Prakash Nair / Mehta</h3>
                            <div class="character-role">The Relentless Inquirer</div>
                            <p class="character-desc">
                                A sharp, weary, and highly intuitive lead investigator who handles the high-profile Malhotra murder case. Unmoved by the seamless, poetic evidence presented to him, he recognizes that perfect stories do not exist and searches for the microscopic heartbeat within the lie.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="traits-wrapper">
                            <span class="trait-tag">Skeptical</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Analytical</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Patient</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Perceptive</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="character-card">
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="character-name">Raghav Malhotra</h3>
                            <div class="character-role">The Target of Correction</div>
                            <p class="character-desc">
                                A predatory, heavy-set former government official turned powerful corporate conglomerate leader. His past systemic corruption, embezzlement schemes, and intentional frame-ups drove Aarav's honest father to structural ruin and ultimate self-destruction.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="traits-wrapper">
                            <span class="trait-tag">Arrogant</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Predatory</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Complacent</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Untouchable</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="chapters" class="section-padding">
            <span class="section-label">The Structure</span>
            <h2 class="section-heading">The Architectural Blueprints</h2>
            <div class="chapters-grid">
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 1</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">The Genius Among Us</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">
                        Aarav Deshmukh navigates his ritualistic mornings in Valora, exercising surgical control over systems, calculations, and the lab rats of ordinary society who worship his brilliance.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 2</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">Birth of a Shadow</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">
                        A casual comment to a neighbor plants a harmless seed. Through subtle physical contrasts and technological layers, a phantom entity begins to breathe inside human imagination.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 3</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">A Life Divided</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">
                        The boundaries between fiction and fact blur as Aarav orchestrates an elaborate, physical illusion, staging a haunting silhouette for his colleagues to witness with their own eyes.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 4</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">The Enemy</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">
                        An ominous black folder unearths a toxic childhood trauma. The curse of Raghav Malhotra resurfaces, transforming historical grief into cold, unyielding arithmetic.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 5</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">Strings of Fate</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">
                        The murder blueprint is finalized. Synthetic fingerprint impressions, digital breadcrumbs, and manufactured alibis are meticulously aligned on a sprawling board of fate.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 6</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">A Perfect Crime</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">
                        The silent entry into the Malhotra estate executes flawlessly. The target falls, a simulated video drive is inserted, and a nation seamlessly awakens to an engineered truth.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="quotes" class="quotes-bg">
            <div class="section-padding">
                <span class="section-label">The Philosophy</span>
                <h2 class="section-heading">Fragmented Echoes</h2>
                <div class="featured-quote-container">
                    <div class="featured-quote-mark">“</div>
                    <p class="featured-quote-text">
                        "Humans believe in what feels consistent, not in what's true. Consistency is god. I am its priest."
                    </p>
                    <span class="featured-quote-author">— The Mastermind's Journal</span>
                </div>
                <div class="quotes-grid">
                    <div class="quote-card">
                        <p class="quote-text">"Free will is the comfort lie of chaos. It makes people feel important while their actions remain predictable."</p>
                        <span class="quote-context">Lecture at the University</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="quote-card">
                        <p class="quote-text">"People believe what they expect to believe. Provide contrast—create duality and they will fill in the blanks themselves."</p>
                        <span class="quote-context">Reflections on Experimentation</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="quote-card">
                        <p class="quote-text">"Belief is the easiest currency to counterfeit... and belief is the purest form of control."</p>
                        <span class="quote-context">The Counterfeit Breakthrough</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="quote-card">
                        <p class="quote-text">"Vengeance is not chaos—it's correction. The law failed. Emotion failed. But reason never does."</p>
                        <span class="quote-context">Mapping the Retribution</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="quote-card">
                        <p class="quote-text">"Every lie, no matter how perfect, leaves behind a heartbeat."</p>
                        <span class="quote-context">The Inspector's Conviction</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="quote-card">
                        <p class="quote-text">"Words are the most powerful drug used by mankind. And the world... it's beautifully addicted."</p>
                        <span class="quote-context">The Morning After the Verdict</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="journey" class="section-padding">
            <span class="section-label">The Progression</span>
            <h2 class="section-heading">The Algorithm of Retribution</h2>
            <div class="timeline-container">
                <div class="timeline-node">
                    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <span class="timeline-stage">Stage 1: The Thesis</span>
                        <h3 class="timeline-title">The Scientist and the Lab Rats</h3>
                        <p class="timeline-desc">
                            Aarav establishes his absolute intellectual superiority in Valora, evaluating human behavior through mathematical models and rejecting the concept of free will.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-node">
                    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <span class="timeline-stage">Stage 2: The Seed</span>
                        <h3 class="timeline-title">Whispers in the Corridor</h3>
                        <p class="timeline-desc">
                            A casual comment to a neighbor introduces a fictional, problematic brother. The rumor spreads naturally, validating the theory that ambiguity breeds fertile imagination.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-node">
                    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <span class="timeline-stage">Stage 3: The Projection</span>
                        <h3 class="timeline-title">The Silhouette in the Room</h3>
                        <p class="timeline-desc">
                            A physical manifestation is staged. Shadows are cast for colleagues to witness through a half-lit room, supported by physical evidence like dual toothbrushes and pre-recorded phone lines.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-node">
                    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <span class="timeline-stage">Stage 4: The Core Objective</span>
                        <h3 class="timeline-title">The Legacy of Poison</h3>
                        <p class="timeline-desc">
                            A black dossier reveals the whereabouts of Raghav Malhotra, the corrupt official who framed Aarav's father. The psychological game aligns with absolute, mathematical correction.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-node">
                    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <span class="timeline-stage">Stage 5: The Execution</span>
                        <h3 class="timeline-title">The Incision of Justice</h3>
                        <p class="timeline-desc">
                            The corporate fortress is breached using signal jammers and biometric anomalies. Malhotra is neutralized, and a structural trail of clues is set up to lead straight to the phantom.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-node">
                    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <span class="timeline-stage">Stage 6: The Inevitable Friction</span>
                        <h3 class="timeline-title">The Heartbeat in the Narrative</h3>
                        <p class="timeline-desc">
                            Inspector Prakash Nair and colleague Nisha identify microscopic anomalies. A trap is sprung at an abandoned factory, forcing the mastermind to confront the survival phase of his own script.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="ending-section">
            <div class="ending-container">
                <span class="section-label">The Resolution</span>
                <h2 class="ending-title">Knowledge Without Proof</h2>
                <p class="ending-message">
                    Though relentless inquiries circle the truth and modern investigators identify the brilliant pattern of manipulation, the framework remains completely unbreakable. The laws of consensus hold fast. The world continues to hunt a phantom ghost while the architect stands in plain sight—unseen, untouched, and utterly believed.
                </p>
                <div class="ending-quote">
                    "The genius is never cornered... not when he writes the rules."
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="footer">
        <div class="footer-title">THE PHANTOM TWIN</div>
        <div class="footer-author">The Genius Among Us</div>
        <div class="footer-quote">
            "The genius among us was never one of us at all. He was the experiment, and we were the data."
        </div>
    </footer>

    <script>
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
            const navToggle = document.getElementById('navToggle');
            const navLinks = document.getElementById('navLinks');
            const links = navLinks.querySelectorAll('a');

            // Toggle Mobile Menu
            navToggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
                navLinks.classList.toggle('active');
                navToggle.textContent = navLinks.classList.contains('active') ? '×' : '≡';
            });

            // Close Mobile Menu on Link Click
            links.forEach(link => {
                link.addEventListener('click', () => {
                    if (navLinks.classList.contains('active')) {
                        navLinks.classList.remove('active');
                        navToggle.textContent = '≡';
                    }
                });
            });

            // Smooth Scroll adjustment for Sticky Header
            links.forEach(anchor => {
                anchor.addEventListener('click', function (e) {
                    e.preventDefault();
                    const targetId = this.getAttribute('href');
                    if(targetId === '#') return;
                    
                    const targetElement = document.querySelector(targetId);
                    if (targetElement) {
                        const navHeight = document.querySelector('.navbar').offsetHeight;
                        const targetPosition = targetElement.getBoundingClientRect().top + window.pageYOffset - navHeight;
                        
                        window.scrollTo({
                            top: targetPosition,
                            behavior: 'smooth'
                        });
                    }
                });
            });

            // Navbar adjustments on scroll
            window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
                const navbar = document.querySelector('.navbar');
                if (window.scrollY > 50) {
                    navbar.style.backgroundColor = 'rgba(10, 11, 13, 0.98)';
                } else {
                    navbar.style.backgroundColor = 'rgba(10, 11, 13, 0.95)';
                }
            });
        });
    </script>
    <%- include('partials/footer') %>